<FIRST>r i PM-Philippines-Storm     06-06 0154</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Philippines-Storm,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Storm Dot Hits Central Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tropical storm Dot hit the central
Philippines today with heavy rain and 47 mph winds, officials said.
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties.
   Chief weather forecaster Eduardo Parong said the center of the
storm came ashore at the southern tip of Samar island, about 410
miles southeast of Manila. The storm was moving west northwest at
14 mph, he said.
   A weather bulletin said the storm, the third to hit the
Philippines this year, dumped rain over a wide area stretching from
Bataan province west of Manila across Manila Bay to northern
Mindanao. The coast guard said it prevented ships from leaving
various ports.
   There were no reports of damage or casualties from Samar or the
neighboring island of Leyte, which also lay in the storm's path.
Such reports take days to reach the capital because of poor
communications.
</TEXT>
