<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Philippines-Coup     06-06 0169</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Philippines-Coup,0174</SECOND>
<HEAD>Army Major Acquitted of Participating in Coup Plot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A military court on Tuesday acquitted
an army major of charges that he took part in an attempt to
overthrow the government of President Corazon Aquino in 1987.
   The five-man military tribunal said the prosecution failed to
produce evidence that Maj. Horacio Lactao disregarded lawful orders
from a superior officer.
   Lactao led about 30 soldiers aboard a column of tanks and
armored personnel carriers from the army training camp in Nueva
Ecija province to Manila at the height of the bloodiest of six coup
attempts against Mrs. Aquino.
   The coup on Aug. 28, 1987, left at least 53 people dead and
hundreds others wounded.
   Military troops loyal to Mrs. Aquino blocked Lactao's group
before it entered Manila. Lactao said he did not violate any orders
when he led the convoy back to the training camp on his own.
   Last year, Lactao and his men were cleared by another court
martial of charges of mutiny.
</TEXT>
