<HEAD>LA to Keep Music Awards Show for Another Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Grammy Awards show will stay here in 1990
rather than return to New York, the head of the National Academy of
Recording Arts and Sciences said.
   The Grammys were moved from Los Angeles to New York in 1988, then
came back in 1989, and it was widely expected the show would
alternate between the entertainment capitals.
   But NARAS President Michael Green said Monday that Los Angeles'
``stellar'' efforts as host of this year's show had impressed
organizers. ``Los Angeles did a great job, so we're rewarding them
and ourselves by coming back.''
