<HEAD>Dustin Hoffman is Finally a Graduate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA MONICA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dustin Hoffman is going to be a
graduate.
   The Oscar-winning star of ``Rain Man'' and ``Kramer vs. Kramer''
is to receive an honorary degree from his alma mater, Santa Monica
College, which he credits with pointing him toward an acting career.
   The college board voted unanimously Monday to give an honorary
associate in arts degree to Hoffman, who enrolled in the college to
study music in 1955 but changed to theater arts classes. He never
graduated.
   Superintendent Richard Moore said Hoffman sent word through his
agent that he would be honored to accept the degree. Hoffman is
currently appearing in London as Shylock in ``The Merchant of
Venice.''
   Details of when and where the degree will be presented will be
worked out between Hoffman's agent and college officials, Katz said.
   After graduating from Los Angeles High School in 1955, Hoffman
took his first classes in what was then called Santa Monica City
College.
   Hoffman has been nominated six times for Academy Awards,
including ``The Graduate,'' ``Midnight Cowboy,'' ``Lenny'' and
``Tootsie.''
