<HEAD>Astrue Picked for HHS Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Tuesday he will nominate
Michael J. Astrue to become general counsel of the Department of
Health and Human Services.
   Astrue has been an associate counsel at the White House since
1988 and held posts at HHS from 1985 to 1988. He is a 1978 graduate
of Yale and a 1983 graduate of Harvard Law School.
   The nomination is subject to Senate confirmation.
</TEXT>
