<DOCNO> AP890606-0129 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-06-89 2009EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-Oliwa     06-06 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Oliwa,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Deputy Defense Minister Oliwa Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Deputy Defense Minister Wlodzimierz Oliwa
has died, the official PAP news agency reported Tuesday. He was 64.
   Oliwa, the army's chief quartermaster and a member of Parliament
from 1976-85, died Monday, the agency said. It did not give the
cause of death.
   Oliwa, who had served in the army since 1945, held numerous
military and government posts.
   He was a member of the Military Council of National Salvation,
which administered martial law that was imposed Dec. 13, 1981, and
used to suppress the Solidarity union movement. Solidarity was
subsequently outlawed and martial law lifted.
   Solidarity was legalized again under an April 5 agreement between
the independent union and Communist authorities and scored major
victories in Sunday's elections.
</TEXT>
