<HEAD>Storm Strikes Central Philippines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tropical storm Dot struck the central
Philippines with heavy rain and 47 mph winds Tuesday.
   There were no reports of damage or casualties from Samar, where
the storm went ashore, or the neighboring island of Leyte, also lay
in Dot's path. Such reports usually take days to reach the capital
because of poor communications.
   Chief weather forecaster Eduardo Parong said the storm hit land
at the southern tip of Samar, about 400 miles southeast of Manila,
and began moving west-northwest at 14 mph.
   A weather bulletin said Dot, the third tropical storm in the
Philippines this year, dumped rain over a wide area from Bataan
province west of Manila across Manila Bay to northern Mindanao. The
coast guard said it prevented ships from leaving several ports.
