<FIRST>r w AM-Bush-Arts     06-06 0084</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bush-Arts,90</SECOND>
<HEAD>N.Y. Legislator Named to Arts Council</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush named New York State Sen. Roy M.
Goodman on Tuesday to the National Council on the Arts.
   Goodman is a 10-term Republican state legislator and former New
York City finance commissioner and treasurer. He served on the
Reagan administration's National Commission of Fine Arts in 1985.
   Goodman will succeed C. Douglas Dillon, retired chairman of the
Smithsonian Institution, on the arts council. His term will run
until Sept. 3, 1994.
</TEXT>
