<FIRST>r i AM-Obit-MrsEndara     06-06 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Obit-Mrs Endara,0092</SECOND>
<HEAD>Opposition Presidential Candidate's Wife Dies of Heart Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PANAMA CITY, Panama (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Marcela Cambra de Endara, wife of
opposition presidential candidate Guillermo Endara, died of a heart
attack Tuesday evening, a spokesman said. She was 48.
   Political opposition spokesman Anel Beliz said Mrs. Endara died
at her home in Panama City.
   He said she had a history of heart trouble.
   Endara and his supporters claim he won the May 7 presidential
election, which was later nullified by the government controlled by
Gen. Manuel Antonio Noriega.
</TEXT>
