<HEAD>EEC Unemployment Lowest In More Than Five Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The unemployment rate in the European
Community fell to 9.3 percent in April, down 0.1 percentage point
from the previous month, the EEC statistics agency said Tuesday.
   Unemployment fell in all of the 12 EEC member nations except
Denmark, West Germany, and Italy, where slight gains were reported.
   Unemployment was highest in Spain, with a 17.9 percent rate, and
lowest in Luxembourg, with a 1.8 percent rate.
