<FIRST>d f BC-Germany-Ivory     06-06 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Germany-Ivory,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>West Germany Bans Import of Ivory from Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The West German government on Tuesday
joined France in banning ivory imports from Africa in an effort to
save African elephants from extinction.
   The ban invoked by the federal Environment Ministry took effect
immediately, a ministry statement said.
   It said the the number of African elephants had dropped to about
700,000 in the last 10 years.
   ``We have to conclude that African elephants are threatened with
extinction,'' the ministry stated.
   France imposed a similar ban over the weekend and the West
German ministry said it expected other European Economic Community
countries to follow suit shortly.
