<FIRST>r f BC-NorthernTelecom     06-06 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Northern Telecom,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Northern Telecome Lays Off 665 In Nashville</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Northern Telecom Inc. will lay off 665
employees in Nashville as part of a massive reorganization
announced last December, company officials say.
   The company's Nashville office complex, which had 850 full-time
and part-time employees at the beginning of this year, will be
reduced to about 185 workers by year's end as its manufacturing
segment is shut down, the officials confirmed Monday.
   Spokesman Jeff Benson said many high-tech jobs and equipment
will be moved to other states, although the firm's headquarters and
a telephone refurbishing operation will remain in Nashville.
   The majority will go to Santa Clara, Calif., and Research
Triangle Park near Raleigh, N.C., Benson said.
   Northern Telecom Inc. is a subsidiary of Northern Telecom Ltd.,
which announced a reorganization Dec. 6 to cut employment worldwide
by 5 percent. Northern Telecom Ltd., based in Toronto, has 50,000
employees worldwide and 22,000 in the United States. Total revenues
last year were $5.4 billion, with two-thirds of that coming from
U.S. operations.
</TEXT>
